    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/_i6mh0jIqiJXLEyh076MtFy-/image.png\">image.png</a><br>\nWhy did it give me False instead of \"¬t ∈ G\", which I could then use to prove the goal. I don't see any contradictions in the assumptions themselves.</p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/3121/_i6mh0jIqiJXLEyh076MtFy-/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/3121/_i6mh0jIqiJXLEyh076MtFy-/image.png\"></a></div><p>Edit: Turned out it gave me another goal. Case 1 had assumption \"false\" and Case 2 had \"not t in G\". That makes sense.</p>",
